Recipe by the one and only @chancy.james ♥️ swipe for some highlights 😅
"How to" video on IGTV!

TAG Your ppl and grab recipe below! 

RECIPE 
Makes two Wellington loaves! Perfect for freezing & baking later too!

Ingredients 
1-2 tbs oil (I used avocado oil)
1 yellow onion (diced)
4 garlic cloves (minced)
8oz of mushrooms (1 container, diced)
2 “ribs” of celery (diced small)
3/4 cup frozen peas
1 (12 oz) package vegan ground “beef” (I used Impossible meat)
1 package of Puff Pastry (includes 2 doughs)
2 tbs cornstarch
2 tbs ground flax w/ 6 tbs water
1/3 tsp salt
1/4 tsp pepper (or grind to liking)
1 tbs dried basil
1 tbs dried thyme 

1. Takeout Puff Pasty dough and vegan ground “beef” to defrost.

2. On medium heat sauté diced onion and garlic for about 2 minutes. Add diced mushroom. Sauté for about 2 more minutes. Add frozen peas and diced celery.

3. Add vegan “beef”, sauté for about 5-7 minutes...You do not need to cook the whole way, anything that is not finished cooking will cook through in the oven.

4. Take mixture off heat and put into a large mixing bowl to cool. Add 2 tbs cornstarch and mix in.

5. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

6. In a small bowl or cup, Mix 2 tbs of ground flax with 6 tbs water. Let sit for 10-15 min while mixture cools. Then add the flax mixture to the "meat" mixture & mix to combine !

7. Once mixture is cool, roll out two puff pastry doughs. Roll gently to evenly spread into large rectangular loaf.

8. Cut slits along side, you will go about 3 inches on each side. Distribute mixture evenly between two puff pastry’s. Fold over slits to create a lattice criss cross design.Tuck in each end to secure mixture.

9. Bake in oven at 400 degrees for 40 minutes or until deep Golden brown. 

10. Let cool for 10 minutes and use bread or serrated knife to slice. Enjoy with Mushroom Gravy or on its own!

CREAMY VEGAN CHIPOTLE PASTA w/ CRISPY BREADED MUSHROOMS 🤍
Save recipe & tag your ppl !😍
RECIPE
12 ounces pasta of choice 
Extra virgin olive oil

Sauce: 
Small (white or yellow) onion, diced small
4 garlic cloves, Minced
1/2 block soft tofu 
2-3 chipotle peppers from a can (they’re really spicy)
2 tbsp nutritional yeast 
1/4 cup + 2 tbsp water
2 tbsp vegan butter 

Crispy mushrooms:
1 cup regular all purpose flour OR Brown rice flour 
3/4- 1 cup non dairy milk 
1 tsp ground paprika 
1 tsp garlic powder 
1 cup bread crumbs 
1 tbsp Italian seasonings 
8 ounces mushrooms of choice, I used king oyster mushrooms 
Oil for frying 

FOR THE PASTA

1. Cook pasta according to package. Make sure to salt your water! 
2. To a pan over medium/ low heat add in 2 tbsp extra virgin oil. Saute onions for 2 minutes then add in garlic and saute for 5-7 minutes then add to a blender with 1/2 a block of soft tofu, pinch of salt, nutritional yeast, filtered water & chipotle peppers… start with 2 then add another couple if you want it spicier! 
3. To the same pan you cooked the onions and garlic add 2 tbsp vegan butter. Keep on medium to low heat. Once melted add in the sauce, cook for 3-4 minutes on low heat then add in cooked noodles. Toss to combine.

FOR THE CRISPY BREADED MUSHROOMS

INSTRUCTIONS
1.Pour enough oil in a wok or pot, about 1-2 inches deep of oil. Heat on medium-high. 

2.Prepare batter. Mix flour, salt, paprika and garlic powder & then add almond milk. Stir with a whisk or fork until well combined.
In another bowl add bread crumbs and Italian seasonings. Mix to combine. 

3.Add sliced mushroom one at a time to the batter to coat. Shake off excess then roll into the bread crumbs and place on  plate 

4.Once your oil is ready  add  a coupe mushrooms at a time . Rotate carefully after 1-2 minutes. Cook for a total of 3-4 minutes. Or until both sides are golden and crisp. Place in a plate lined with paper towels and sprinkle With salt.

TAQUITOS DE PAPA W/ CREAMY SALSA VERDE
Crispy rolled potato tacos in a creamy tomatillo salsa, PERFECT for this weekend! TAG your people & save recipe below!

RECIPE
Makes 8-12 rolled tacos, depends on the size of your tortillas! 
1 1/2 lbs yukon gold potatoes, peeled
2 tbsp vegan butter 
2-3 tbsp plain non dairy milk
Pinch of salt
1 tsp garlic powder 
1/2 tsp ground pepper 
8-2 corn tortillas 
Avocado oil or oil of choice for (high heat) frying 

Creamy Tomatillo salsa:
1/2 cup raw cashews 
1/4 cup water
1 lb tomatillos 
Pinch of salt
3 garlic gloves 
1-2 Serrano peppers 
Small handful of cilantro 
(Optional) vegan sour cream or vegan crema

Instructions:
1.Steam or boil peeled and chopped potatoes for 15-20 minutes until fork tender and cooked all the way. In a bowl add cooked potatoes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, vegan butter and non dairy milk. Mash to combine. 

2.Heat tortillas slightly so that they are bendable. I usually wrap a stalk of tortillas in a dish towel and microwave for 30-45 seconds until soft. Or you can heat them individually on a pan.

3.Add 2-3 tbsp potatoes to the center of a tortilla and roll it up. Don’t let too much of the potato near the edge.

4.Add enough oil to the bottom of a pan (about 2 inches) and fry for 2-3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. BE CAREFUL frying!  Add your crispy tacos to a plate lined with paper towels. Do this in batches letting a little room in between each taco. 
You can also bake them at 375 for 10 minutes… just brush with a little oil on both sides.

5.For the creamy salsa roast peeled tomatillos until charred on both sides and in a pot combine cashews, Serrano and garlic cloves and boil for 15—20 minutes ( you can Also boil these along with the potatoes to make it easier). Add the boil cashews, Serrano pepper (stem removed), garlic, tomatillos, a pinch of salt, 1/4 cup water and handful of cilantro to a blender and blend on high! Blend until smooth. Taste and add more salt if needed

6.To serve, add a few spoonfuls of salsa to plate, then add your rolled tacos, top off with more sauce and crema!

AGUA DE JAMAICA 
Because it always comes to the rescue 🥲 
There are so many great benefits to drinking agua de Jamaica (hibiscus tea) 🤍 

Tag your ppl!

If you want to make a big batch for the week:
1 cup dried hibiscus 
6-7 cups water 
Cane sugar or sweetener of choice (sweeten to your liking) 

You can steep in room temp water for a few hours or over night (how my mom does it :) 

OR 

Add about 2-3 cups boiling hot water to the hibiscus, let it steep for 10 minutes then add 3 more cups of room temp water 

Sweeten to your liking and pour over ice!

HUEVOS A LA MEXICANA Vegan style! 
Inspired by my dad making scrambled eggs (with that Mexican touch of tomatoes, chili and onion) for me when I was young 🥲

RECIPE
•Just vegan egg (or you can use soft tofu)
•1 tsp Garlic powder 
•1 tsp dried chives 
•Pinch Black Salt/  kala namak (this salt adds an egg like flavor…you can use regular sea salt too!)
•Fresh black pepper 
•1/4 onion, diced small 
•3 cloves garlic, minced 
•1 Roma tomato, seeds removed & diced small
•Serrano pepper, seeds removed & diced small
•Tortillas of choice
•Avocado 
•Vegan cheese of choice (I used violife feta because it tasted like queso fresco to me)
•refried beans (recipe can be found in most recent post)
•grilled Nopales (optional, let me know if you want a recipe for the nopales )
•cilantro 
•salsa 

1. In a pan over medium/ low heat add a tbsp of oil or vegan butter, then sauté onion, garlic, tomato and Serrano for 5-7 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
2. Add the “vegan just egg” to a bowl & add garlic powder, dried chives, pinch of black salt or regular salt & black pepper. Mix to combine. 
3. Once the tomato mixture has cooked for 6-7 minutes move the mixture to the edges, and in the center of the pan add a bit more of oil or vegan butter then once melted, add in the vegan egg. Cook on low heat, slowly moving it all around. 
4. * you can also use tofu instead… make sure once you have crumbled tofu to season well with the same seasonings + 1/2 -1 tsp ground turmeric !
5. Assemble your tacos with cooked / warm tortillas, adding avocado, salsa, beans, nopales & whatever else you want!

REFRIED BEANS 
Tag your people and please start making your own beans at home 😇 

RECIPE 
*if you want to make fast refried beans you can use canned pinto beans* 

3 cups of Peruvian or pinto (dried) beans 
1 white onion
6 cloves garlic
2-3 tbsp neutral oil 
Salt to taste 
1-2 jalapeños 
1 tsp better than bouillon (vegetarian chicken) 
Filtered water

Sort through your beans and remove any pebbles or small rocks. You may find 1-2 in each batch of beans. Strain your beans really well then add to pot. 

Cover the beans with filtered water, you want about 1-2 inches of water above the beans. Add in 3/4 of onion (cut in big chunks) and peeled whole garlic cloves. 

Do not add salt yet, we will add later.

With the lid off, cook the beans for around 2 hours or more or until the beans are fully cooked, soft and tender. Throughout the cooking process you will need to add 2-3 cups of additional (HOT) filtered water as the water in the pot will begin to evaporate.

Once the beans are cooked and tender add a generous 2 pinches of salt, mix then taste, add more salt to your liking.

Chop the remaining white onion and jalapeños… remove the seeds! 
In a pan add 2-3 tbsp oil. Then sauté the onion and jalapeño for a few minutes. Add in atleast 3 cups of cooked beans, if some of the juice comes with that’s ok! 

Im a cup combine 1 tsp of bouillon paste + 4 tbsp warm water. Mix to dissolve then add into beans. Mash beans, taste… add salt to your liking and enjoy!

STRAWBERRY HIBISCUS COCKTAIL 
Tag your ppl & make this weekend 🤍

Bartender Chance with a delish cocktail recipe we served at our engagement party 😍 

The most refreshing cocktail with the perfect balance of flavors, subtle sweetness from the @castrawberries &tartness from the hibiscus 🌺 #ad 

RECIPE
For the tea:
Makes enough for about 10 cocktails 
1 cup dried hibiscus
flowers 6 cups filtered
cold water
1/2 lb California Strawberries, sliced

For the cocktail:
(Serves 2)
2-3 ounces tequila
2 limes, cut into
quarters 1 ounce of
simple syrup
3-4 drops of orange bitters
4 ounces strawberry hibiscus
tea Ice to shake
(Optional) hibiscus margarita salt

Directions - List detailed step-by-step
instructions for preparation, cooking, and
serving, including equipment (e.g., number
and size of pans), oven temperature and
cooking time.

1. In a pot add 2 cups of water a bring to a
boil then add in the dried hibiscus
flowers and boil for 5 minutes. Strain
into a pitcher…at this point you can
choose to add sugar or keep
unsweetened.
2. Add in 4 cups of cold water. Mix to
combine then add in sliced
strawberries. Let it sit 10 minute while
you prepare your cocktail ingredients
3. Pour margarita salt on a plate. Line the
rim of a glass with lime and then dunk the
rim in the salt.
4. To the cocktail shaker add ice, tequila,
simple syrup, orange bitter, strawberry
hibiscus tea. Add lid and shake well.
5. Add fresh ice to your glass and pour in
drink. Top off with additional fresh

MEXICAN RED RICE 
Red rice is a staple in Mexican cuisine. It can seem a little intimidating but truly so easy with the right tips and tricks! 

Peep my stories for some more tips 🤍

#ad You only need a few ingredients and we are using @osterkitchen one touch blender (available at Walmart) for a quick broth hack and red salsa recipe for the rice! #osterpartner #blendlesspossibilities 

RECIPE
Feeds 5-6 
Ingredients: 
1 cup white jasmine rice
2 ripe large roma tomatoes (make sure they’re deep red and on the softer side) 1/2 white onion 2 garlic cloves
2 cups vegetable broth (or water + 1 tsp bouillon)
Couple tbsp any oil 

Instructions:
1. Rinse rice really well and let it dry as much as possible. 

2. Make broth if using bouillon if not measure out 2 cups broth 

3. Chop 1/4 onion really small and set aside. Then with the other 1/4 of an onion chop into big chunks and place into a blender followed by the 2 ripe roma tomatoes and 2 garlic cloves. Blend on high for 1 minute. 

4. Add 2 tbsp oil to pan then add rice (rice should be mostly dried, Add rice and cook on high heat constantly moving it around for 4-5 minutes...DO NOT TAKE YOUR EYES OFF RICE, 
KEEP MOVING IT AROUND. Then once golden add onion. Cook for 2 minutes continuing to move around in pan. 

5. Add the tomato sauce and cook for 4 minutes moving constantly then add broth, Bring to a simmer, will take 2 minutes. Then cover, bring to lowest heat and cook for 17-22 minutes or until all the liquid is evaporated and rice is perfectly cooked.

POBLANO PEPPER CREMA 
Amazing on just about anything🥲 

Recipe 
2 poblano peppers 
2 jalapeños 
1 cup cashews 
Pinch of salt 
1/2 white onion 
3 garlic cloves 
Handful of cilantro 

1. Soak cashews in hot water for at least 10 minutes. 

2. Roast poblanos peppers & jalapeños until charred over open flame or you can roast them in an air fryer for 6-9 minutes at 400F!

3.  Put the peppers in a bowl and cover with plastic and let sit for 5 minutes. 

4. In a pan char onion (roughly chopped) and garlic. 

5. Peel and remove seeds from peppers then place in blender with onion, garlic, cilantro, good pinch salt and (drained) cashews. Add 1/2 cup oh hot water and blend on high until smooth. Add more water if needed!

6. Store in a jar sealed in fridge for up to 6 days. Use on sandwiches, burgers, & of course tacos!

FROZEN MEXICAN HOT CHOCOLATE 
Chocolate, cinnamon & vanilla slushy! SO BEYOND DELISH

I am in love with all that Mexican hot chocolate has to offer, but with this summer heat this is the solution 😙

It’s perfectly sweet, satisfying and delish and refreshing. 
#Osterpartner I have teamed up with @osterkitchen ! 

Using @osterkitchen One Touch Blender available at Walmart! #Blendlesspossiblities

RECIPE

2 ounces dark chocolate, chopped 
1 tbsp cocoa powder 
2 cups oat milk (or any non dairy milk) 
1 cinnamon stick (or 1/4 tsp ground cinnamon)
1 tsp vanilla extract 
2 tbsp pure maple syrup 
Small pinch of salt 
Couple handfuls of ice 

In a pot combine 1 cup of non dairy milk,dark chocolate, cinnamon, vanilla, cocoa powder & pure maple syrup …mix over medium / low heat and let the chocolate fully melt. Remove cinnamon stick 

In a @osterkitchen One-Touch Blender add a cup of non dairy milk, the chocolate mixture, and a couple handfuls of ice. Blend in high until slushy consistency is reached. Enjoy!

ROASTED GARLIC HERB BUTTER 🧈 
Who else has a love for butter in a flour tortilla 🤍 

RECIPE 
1 head of garlic 
1 tbsp olive oil 
1 stick of vegan butter (I used earth balance)
1 tsp dried oregano 
1 tsp dried thyme 
1 tsp dried basil 

Take vegan butter out from the fridge to let it softened / come to room temp.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. 

Cut a bit off the top of a whole garlic head. Then add to a piece of foil and drizzle with olive oil. Wrap it up and bake it oven for 45 minutes or until golden surface forms. 

To a bowl add softened butter, squeeze roasted garlic in, add dried herbs, mix well and enjoy straight away or wrap in plastic wrap whatever way you want and pop in freezed for 35 mins or fridge for an hour to harden up. 

Use in pasta, on bread,
Flour tortillas and Store remaining in fridge!
